**Fixed Deposit (FD)** requires a one-time lumpsum investment, while **Recurring Deposit (RD)** involves fixed monthly deposits. If you have a lumpsum available, FD generally outperforms RD at the same rate because the entire principal earns interest from day one. RD suits those with regular monthly savings rather than a lumpsum.
